NGH CHM KHC G

WOOD ENGRAVING CRAFT

Ngh chm khc g vo th k XVII, ny sinh trn vng t
Si Gn - Gia nh do nhng lu dn ngi Vit v ngi Hoa vo
nh c mang theo. Nhu cu xy dng cc cng trnh kin trc
ngh thut v cng trnh dn dng ca mt vng t mi hnh thnh mt i ng th chm khc g c tay ngh cao.

Chm khc g gm cc k thut: Chm lng, chm chm, chm ni.
thc hin mt cng trnh, ngh nhn cn phi to hnh trn g,
chm khc, sn sa ri mi lp rp. Th trng tiu th sn phm ca ngh chm khc g Si Gn trc kia ch yu p ng nhu cu ni a. Gn y sn phm chm khc g c xut khu sang nhiu nc trn th gii.

Wood - engraving was present in Saigon - Gia Dinh in the 17th century by the Vietnamese and Chinese immigrants. Due to the demands of art construction and activities they formed the professionally skilled engravers in Saigon.

Wood - engraving techniques include cut-out carving, intaglio, alto-relievo. For completing a work, a carver has to draw in wood, engraving, repairing, painting and reassembling. Wood - Engravings were produced for domestic demands. Today, they are exported.
